==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Insuetude
<hw>In"sue*tude</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>insuetudo</ets>, from <ets>insuetus</ets> unaccustomed; pref.
<ets>in-</ets> not + <ets>suetus</ets>, p. p. of <ets>suescere</ets> to
be accustomed.]</ety> <def>The state or quality of being unaccustomed;
absence of use or habit.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Absurdities are great or small in proportion to custom or
<qex>insuetude</qex>.</q> <rj><qau>Landor.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Insufferable</ent>⟦br⟧
